# Magyar Codebase Overview

Hungarian language learning app built with React 19 + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind v4 + Supabase.

## Feature Areas
- **Conjugator** — fill-in-the-blank verb conjugation quiz (`Conjugator.tsx`, `QuizPrefsForm.tsx`)
- **Flash Cards** — FSRS spaced-repetition with Supabase images (`FlashCard.tsx`, `CreateFlashCard.tsx`)
- **Grammar Lessons** — static lessons in `src/components/grammar/`
- **Phrasebook** — static phrase reference (`Phrasebook.tsx`)

## Key Tech
- Routing: `react-router-dom` v7, configured in `App.tsx`
- Backend: Supabase only — two tables (`flashcards`, `review_logs`), one storage bucket (`cardimages`); no auth (anon key)
- Forms: `@tanstack/react-form` + `zod` validation
- Spaced repetition: `ts-fsrs` used exclusively in `FlashCard.tsx`; single module-level `fsrs()` instance (`const f = fsrs()`)
- UI primitives: shadcn/ui pattern (`src/components/ui/`) on top of Radix + Tailwind
- Icons: `lucide-react`; toasts: `sonner`

## State & Persistence
- `localStorage`: conjugator quiz state — `"randomWord"`, `"quizWords"` (via `useLocalStorage.ts`)
- `sessionStorage`: `"completedQuizWords"` — clears on tab close
- Static data (conjugations, phrases, alphabet) imported as bundled JSON — no network call

